article.description: Samardo Samuels scored 14 points and Edgar Sosa 13 to lead Louisville to a 68-59 victory over DePaul on Saturday.
article.headline: DePaul loses eighth straight as Louisville wins third in row
article.linkText: DePaul's skid hits eight with loss to Louisville
article.story: ROSEMONT, Ill. -- Samardo Samuels scored 14 points and Edgar Sosa 13 to lead Louisville to a 68-59 victory over DePaul on Saturday. The victory was the third straight for the Cardinals (18-9, 9-5 Big East), who opened the week with a 66-60 upset of No. 5 Syracuse. The loss was the eighth straight for DePaul (8-18, 1-13). Mac Koshwal paced the Blue Demons with a game-high 26 points, tying a career high. He added 10 rebounds. A large contingent of Louisville fans -- about half the house -- watched the Cardinals use an 11-2 run late in the second half to turn a 49-48 deficit into a 59-50 lead with 3:05 to play. The Cardinals led 32-27 after a first half that included four lead changes, the last with 6:35 left when Kyle Kuric hit a 3-pointer for a 22-21 Louisville edge. Kuric had seven first-half points and Samuels 12.
